                  </hi>. I live in Gilbert-street, Grosvenor-square, and am a pawnbroker. About three o'clock on the 19th of April, I observed the prisoner coming out of one of the boxes of my shop—I thought she looked very poorly—I asked if she had been in the boxes to be served—she said she had—she was brought back soon after with this hearth-rug—it is mine—I had not sold it.</p>
